ExpressJS:
    Framework cho nodejs
nodemon:
    nodemon is a tool that helps develop Node.js based applications by automatically restarting the node application 
    when file changes in the directory are detected.
    INSTALL:
        - Method 1: npm install -g nodemon # or using yarn: yarn global add nodemon (globally)
        - Method 2: npm install --save-dev nodemon # or using yarn: yarn add nodemon -D (only for development period)
            If you use method 2 to install, the nodemon will not be available in system path, we must use npm start to run
            Add start in script. Example:
                "scripts": {
                    "start": "nodemon --inspect index.js",
                    "test": "echo \"Error: no test specified\" && exit 1"
                }             

